The paper discusses a cloud-based architecture for offloading computational resources from robots, which is a topic related to robotics (cs.RO). The use of cloud technologies and algorithms for processing data volumes suggests a connection to distributed computing (cs.DC) and cloud computing (cs.CC). The implementation of mathematical models for accurate processing of data volumes suggests a connection to systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the proposed system architecture allows developers and engineers not specialized in robotic implementation environments to utilize generic robotic algorithms and services off-the-shelf, which suggests a connection to software engineering (cs.SE).
